UI
    Grid based game where you can capture grids to add more people and eventually conquor worlds


Game Design
    Civ 0 - Societal
        Each sector gives a select resource per second
            Energy can be used to upgrade a tile



    Civ 1 - Planetary
		Unlock time travel
			lose all progress, but gain a speed bonus from tacheon particles (currency)


    Civ 2 - Stellar
		Create simulation, similar to challenges of itrtg
            Create alternate universes where you can gain bonuses from completing challenges


    Civ 3 - Gallactic
        Create black holes
			allows player to research FTL travel  	
				
				
	Civ 4 - Universal
        Create Anihilation event -- false vaccum
			Creates a vacuum state higgs field, causing universe to reset
				ultimate game reset, but unlocks civ 4
				
				









Production
    Have base tick speed 1 sec = 1 hour


Research 		(B) - battle 	(P) - population 	(E) - energy
    Tech Tree
		Stage 0: Primates
			Stone Tools (B)
				Cleaning Animals (P)
				Hut Construction (P)
			Fire (E,B)
				Cooking meat (P)
				Clothing (P,B)
		
		Stage 1: Hunter-gatherer nomads
			String (B
		
		Stage 2: Agricultural Revolution
        


Battle
	Battle alien species on tile using population



Time Travel
    Unlocks once civ level 1 is reached
        Resets to civ level 0, but gives a speed bonus of 2x initial, then increase by logarithmically based on civ level above 1




Statistics
    similar to ITRTG stats page




Guide
    Similar to antimatter dimensions guide




Shop (IAP)
    Speed up time passage by 4x ($0.99)
    Have ads that can speed up time passage for 1 hour and give permenant 1% speed bonus




